TUESDAY MORNING ON THE EARLY SHOW
<http://www.cbsnews.com/sections/earlyshow/main500202.shtml>=20

Harry Smith, Hannah Storm, Julie Chen, and Russ Mitchell anchor THE
EARLY SHOW from New York. Dave Price will bring us the weather.=20

Along with the top news of the day, we will also have the following
stories:=20

ANNA NICOLE'S SISTER: NEW BOOK, PT. 1: In the first of an exclusive
two-part interview, Donna Hogan, sister of Anna Nicole Smith, will join
us to talk about the death of the blonde bombshell. Tuesday morning, in
her first interview since her sister's death, Hogan will join us to
discuss her unauthorized biography of the late actress entitled, Train
Wreck: The Life and Death of Anna Nicole Smith.=20

LOU DOBBS: In the first of his new weekly commentaries, Lou Dobbs,
anchor and managing editor of CNN's Lou Dobbs Tonight, will join us.=20

TWO HEROES who have made a difference: In another installment of our
special series, Second Act, we will take a look at Jim Laws, a
cardiologist from Ohio, and Ed Artis, who began his career as a juvenile
car thief. Ed soon found himself in the Army, where he learned to get
things done in hostile places. It was not long after that he began his
life as a freelance humanitarian. When Ed met Jim in Moscow in 1993, the
two knew they were destined for great things. In Moscow, Ed became a
Knight of Malta, a humanitarian order that dates back to the Crusades.
Jim, already a Knight for his Community Service, became intrigued by
Ed's courage. The two formed Knightsbridge and raise money like any
charity, but their ability to distribute large quantities of aid and
medicine directly to the people at the end of the line is what sets them
apart. Ed Artis and Jim Laws have risked their lives distributing tens
of millions of dollars worth of aid to the needy, and they couldn't be
happier. We'll hear their amazing story Tuesday morning.=20

For information on how you can help Ed Artis and Jim Laws on their next
humanitarian mission to Darfur, go to:=20

OneDollar4Darfur=20
Click Here <http://www.onedollar4darfur.com/>=20=20

For information on the documentary Beyond the Call featuring Ed Artis
and Jim Laws, go to:=20

Beyond The Call The Movie=20
Click Here <http://www.beyondthecallthemovie.com/>=20=20

CHRIS KIMBALL: EASY MAKE AHEAD RECIPES: Cook's Illustrated is the
definitive source for all your questions in the kitchen. And what they
have found out is that preparing a delicious meal does not have to be a
huge undertaking. Now, their latest book, The Best Make-Ahead Recipe,
offers closet o three hundred easy recipes that you can prepare ahead of
time. How can you cook now to save time later? The Best Make-Ahead
Recipe is a cookbook for people who want homemade meals, but don't
always have the time to pull a meal together on a weeknight. These
recipes are ones you can prep in advance - they store well, and cook
well. The book is full of advice on freezing, using leftovers, and other
simple tricks. Tuesday morning, Cook's Illustrated founder and editor
Chris Kimball will join us with recipes from the exciting new make-ahead
recipe cookbook - a must for any cook concerned with time.=20

HOW SAFE IS YOUR DRINKING WATER?: A new study to be released on Tuesday
takes a look at the quality of drinking water across the country. How
safe is your drinking water? The results may surprise you. CBS News
Transportation and Consumer Safety Correspondent Nancy Cordes will join
us with more. She'll also shed some light on the best filtration
products that are available.=20

MARTIN SHORT: On Tuesday, the original cast recording of Martin Short:
Fame Becomes Me, will be released. Joining us to celebrate the release
of his album will be the very funny Martin Short!=20

CONSUMER REPORTS: BEST AND WORST APPLIANCES: Well it turns out that
paying more for your kitchen appliances does not guarantee reliability.
The Consumer Reports Annual Product Reliability Survey identifies the
most and least reliable product brands and the results just may surprise
you. Tuesday morning, we'll take a look at how some of the more popular
kitchen ranges, refrigerators, dishwashers and microwaves fared in the
recent survey. Mandy Walker, Senior Editor of Consumer Reports, will
join us with a roundup of the latest.=20

SHIA LEBEOUF ON DISTURBIA: Actor Shia LaBeouf is one of Hollywood's
hottest rising stars. He first gained attention at age thirteen with his
Emmy winning role on the Disney series Even Stevens. He parlayed that
into a successful film career with a starring role in Holes, and was
soon teaming up with A-listers like Will Smith in I, Robot and Keanu
Reeves in Constantine. Now, LaBeouf has three films being released in
the next three months, including Disturbia, which opens this Friday. The
rising star will join us Tuesday morning to talk about his new film and
newfound success.=20

FURNITURE AND TAXES: With tax season upon us, many of us are looking for
an easy way to reduce some of our out-of-pocket costs. Jennifer Litwin,
author of Furniture Hot Spots and Best Furniture Buying Tips Ever!, and
a contributor to Consumer's Digest magazine, recommends donating gently
used furniture to save money on income taxes. So how can you decide what
items will make the most sizable contributions? Jennifer Litwin will
join us with advice.=20

If you would like more information on any of these stories or the
broadcast, please click on the following address and e-mail us:=20
earlyshow@cbs.com=20

